---
intent: >
  Deliver aidemd.dev as a greenfield Next.js 14 App Router static export -- the
  marketing landing page and docs shell render pixel-for-pixel against the
  Terminal design handoff at 1440px, the docs pipeline generates 33 routes by
  build-time filesystem walk across .aide/docs/, .claude/commands/,
  .claude/agents/, and .claude/skills/ (zero hardcoded lists), Shiki pre-renders
  syntax highlighting at build time with a custom theme keyed off the handoff
  accent palette, and the Expo mascot (renamed from AIDEY) drives scroll-
  contextual tips via IntersectionObserver. Ships to GitHub Pages with GA4 via GTM
  afterInteractive, footer-dot canonical signal, and per-docs cite-as URLs
  pinned to commit hash.
---

## Project Structure

The tree below is the complete proposed state of the repo after this plan
executes. Everything under `src/app/` is new. `.aide/docs/`, `.claude/`, and
`design_handoff_aidemd_site/` already exist -- the first two are read at build
time by the docs pipeline, the third is reference material only and is NOT
shipped.

Three conventions encoded in the tree:

1. **Client vs server components.** Every file annotated `[client]` opens with
   `"use client"`. Everything else is a server component by default. The spec
   requires defaulting to server; only files needing state, refs, or browser
   APIs become client components.
2. **_components/ colocation.** Next.js treats any folder prefixed `_` as
   non-routable. Section-level components for the marketing page live under
   `src/app/_components/` and for docs under `src/app/docs/_components/`.
   Top-level `src/components/` is reserved for primitives consumed by 2+
   unrelated features (Nav, Footer, Expo, CodeBlock, Callout, DocMeta).
3. **Folder-name = default-export.** Every component folder exports one
   default function with the same name as the folder. `Hero/index.tsx` exports
   `Hero`. This is the progressive-disclosure contract.

```
aidemd.dev/                           ← scope root (. in intent.aide)
├── .aide/
│   ├── intent.aide                   [existing] project-level spec
│   ├── plan.aide                     [existing] THIS FILE
