## Prerequisites

Greenfield project -- no upstream modules to coordinate with. Prerequisites are
external:

- **Git repo initialized with at least one commit.** The `resolveCommitHash/`
  helper uses `git log -1 --format=%h -- <file>` at build time. Before step 1
  runs, the scope directory must be `git init`'d and have an initial commit --
  otherwise every docs page falls back to the literal string `'uncommitted'`.
  Step 1 handles this as part of project bootstrap.
- **npm registry reachable.** `npm install` pulls Next 14, Tailwind 4, Shiki 1,
  unified, gray-matter, clsx, tailwind-merge, Vitest, Playwright.
- **Design handoff assets on disk.** `design_handoff_aidemd_site/prototypes/`
  already exists and is the visual source of truth. Assets in
  `prototypes/assets/` (4 PNGs) will be renamed on copy to `public/` in step 3.

## Plan

### 1. Bootstrap project scaffolding, Tailwind v4 theme, and CSS var palette

Read: `coding-playbook/setup/getting-started`, `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`

- [x] 1a. Initialize package.json with Next 14, React 18, Tailwind 4, @tailwindcss/postcss, clsx, tailwind-merge, TypeScript, and the MDX pipeline deps (shiki@1, unified, remark-parse, remark-gfm, remark-rehype, rehype-raw, rehype-stringify, gray-matter). Add dev deps: vitest, @playwright/test, @types/react, @types/node. Scripts: `dev`, `build`, `start`, `preview` (`next build && npx serve out -p 4321`), `test:unit`, `test:visual`, `docs:verify`.
