titles; second person; 1-2 sentences; framework name is `AIDE`, mascot is `Expo` (keep distinct -- never write `AIDEY` or the abandoned interim `AID`); specific to the section's content. Pose choice rules: `point` for tips that direct attention to something on screen ("look at this"); `teach` for explanatory tips; `wave` only for greeting-style tips; `think` for reflective/conceptual tips. Suggested poses: `pipeline → point` (directing to the stage selector); `cliDemo → point` (directing to the terminal); `comparison → think` (the "heavier vs lighter" reflection); `footer → wave` (sign-off); `docs → teach` (the docs are the canonical reference). Final structure: `EXPO_TIPS: Readonly<Record<SectionId, ExpoTip>>` with exactly 10 keys -- `hero`, `threeLayerModel`, `pipeline`, `intentTree`, `vaultBrain`, `cliDemo`, `comparison`, `quickstart`, `footer`, `docs`.
