### 4. Build the docs registry pipeline (filesystem walk → 33 routes)

Read: `coding-playbook/services/service-layer`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`, `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`

- [x] 4a. Create `src/service/docsRegistry/.aide` -- intent sub-spec: scope (the 4 content roots), intent (build the 33-route registry with zero exclusions), outcomes.desired (every .md file discovered becomes a DocRoute; commit hash injected at build time; ordering is deterministic; index.md routes render at the section root), outcomes.undesired (hardcoded page lists anywhere; skipped files; missing commit hashes silently defaulting without marker).
- [x] 4b. Create `src/service/docsRegistry/walkDocsRoot/index.ts` -- recursive walker. Uses `node:fs/promises.readdir(absRoot, { recursive: true, withFileTypes: true })` in Node 22; filters entries where `dirent.isFile() && dirent.name.endsWith('.md')`. Slug derivation: relative path from `absRoot`, strip `.md`, replace path separators with `/`; special-case `index.md` and folder `index.md` patterns (see Decisions). Each entry returns `{ section, slug, title, urlPath: \`/docs/${urlSegment}/${slug}\`, absPath, order: 0 }`. `title` defaults to the first `# ` heading in the file or the slug if none.
- [x] 4c. Create `src/service/docsRegistry/parseDocFrontmatter/index.ts` -- wraps `gray-matter(fileContents)`. If a file has no frontmatter block, returns `{ frontmatter: { title: deriveFromFirstH1(body) ?? slug }, body: fileContents }`. Never throws on missing frontmatter; those files are first-class (the `.claude/commands/*.md` and `.claude/agents/*.md` files are plain markdown without YAML frontmatter).
- [x] 4d. Create `src/service/docsRegistry/resolveCommitHash/index.ts` -- uses `node:child_process.execSync('git log -1 --format=%h -- ' + JSON.stringify(absPath), { encoding: 'utf8' }).trim()`. Returns `'uncommitted'` when stdout is empty (file not yet committed). Wrap in an in-process `Map<string, string>` cache keyed on absPath (commit hashes can't change during a single build).
- [x] 4e. Create `src/service/docsRegistry/orderRoutes/index.ts` -- sort by (1) section priority from DOCS_CATEGORIES order (methodology, commands, agents, skills), (2) `index.md` always first within its section, (3) alphabetical by slug. Assigns `order: i` to each route after sorting.
- [x] 4f. Create `src/service/docsRegistry/renderMarkdown/index.ts` -- unified pipeline: `remark-parse → remark-gfm → remark-rehype (allowDangerousHtml: true) → rehype-raw → rehypeShikiFromHighlighter(shiki, 'aide-theme') → rehype-stringify`. Takes markdown + a prebuilt Highlighter instance. Returns HTML string. Callout and DocMeta rendering is NOT handled here -- those are consumer-side React components; the pipeline only produces plain HTML for paragraphs, lists, inline code, fenced code blocks (with Shiki), tables, headings, blockquotes.
- [x] 4g. Create `src/service/docsRegistry/index.ts` -- orchestrator. Flow: (1) import DOCS_CATEGORIES, (2) for each category, call walkDocsRoot; concat all routes, (3) sort via orderRoutes, (4) return `{ routes, getByKey: (key) => routes.find(r => \`${r.section}/${r.slug}\` === key) }`. JSDoc describes the cascading discovery-ordering-keying flow. Cache: the orchestrator memoizes its own output via a module-level `let cached: DocRegistry | null` so generateStaticParams and every page load the same registry in a single build.
- [x] 4h. Create `src/service/docsRegistry/index.test.ts` -- vitest suite. Mocks `node:fs/promises` and `node:child_process`. Asserts: (i) 33 routes total (numbers breakdown: 9 methodology, 13 commands (aide.md + 12 subcommands), 9 agents, 2 skills), (ii) every `urlPath` matches `/docs/{methodology,commands,agents,skills}/\<slug>`, (iii) ordering puts `docs/methodology/index` first overall, (iv) `uncommitted` fallback works when git stdout is empty.
- [x] 4i. Create `scripts/verify-docs-registry.mjs` -- dynamic-imports the registry and prints a table of (section, slug, urlPath, commit) for humans to diff against `ls -R .aide/docs .claude/commands .claude/agents .claude/skills`. Wire `npm run docs:verify` to it.

**Traces to:** intent.aide "docs page list from a build-time filesystem walk across four content roots ... with zero exclusions", "A hardcoded list of doc pages anywhere in the codebase ... is a spec violation", "cite-as URLs follow the pattern https://aidemd.dev/docs/<slug>?v=<commit>".

**Acceptance:** `npm run docs:verify` prints 33 rows. `npm run test:unit` passes. `buildRegistry()` returns the same routes across repeated calls (memoization).

