Read: `coding-playbook/client/seo`

- [x] 11a. Create `src/components/GlobalScripts/index.tsx` -- server. Reads `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_GTM_ID`; if unset, returns `null`. Otherwise renders one `<Script id="gtm-init" strategy="afterInteractive">` tag with the GTM container snippet. GA4 is configured inside the GTM container (GTM-M24M4PPV), not loaded via gtag.js directly. DNT guard (Option A): the entire GTM init snippet is wrapped in a `navigator.doNotTrack === '1'` check — when DNT is on the container never loads. Also requires the GTM noscript iframe in `layout.tsx` `<body>` for fallback.
- [x] 11b. Create `src/components/CanonicalTag/index.tsx` -- client. `usePathname` + `useEffect` to set/refresh `<link rel="canonical" href={\`https://aidemd.dev${pathname === '/' ? '' : pathname}\`}>`. Static export cannot inject server-side canonical tags (next/metadata's alternates.canonical works but requires SSG + Node rendering per-route; our per-route metadata in docs uses alternates.canonical but this client component is the root-layout fallback for /).
- [x] 11c. Add `src/app/sitemap.ts` -- `export default async function sitemap(): Promise<MetadataRoute.Sitemap>` that returns `/` + `/docs` + every route from `buildRegistry()`.
